; The term "most sought-after flights" refers to flights that have been accessed the most times, implying popularity or high interest among users; 
; The query does not specify any particular time frame for the accesses, so it is assumed to consider all available data; 
; The information gathered provides a comprehensive overview of user engagement with specific flights.

sql:
SELECT airline_name, headquarters
FROM airlines
ORDER BY airline_name ASC;
